cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CV

This paper focuses on the design of secure protocols for machine learning tasks, specifically for training Deep Neural Networks (DNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which deals with secure protocols and privacy-preserving techniques. The paper also involves optimization techniques for DNN training, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves computations and algorithms, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves image recognition tasks, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
